00:29:18,300 --> 00:29:20,800
How 'bout that wake-up call, everybody?

438
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:23,800
OK, we have phone lines. Phone lines are up.

439
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,700
Generator's switching.

440
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:30,200
Emergency power's up.
What you got coming in, Phil?

441
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,900
I got...

442
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:34,900
- Katie, DWP?
- DWP - I'm doing that right now.

443
00:29:35,100 --> 00:29:38,200
- Anybody seen Billy?
- He's stuck on the 10. He's not in yet.

444
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,200
Listen up, people.

445
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:49,800
I want a meeting of all department heads
in exactly five minutes.

446
00:29:50,100 --> 00:29:51,800
That's a very cool hat, Emmit.

447
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:55,700
Thanks. Your wife rolled over
and said the same thing to me this morning.

448
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,900
- Hello.
- That's a pink slip.

449
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,200
Any more quips, or can we work this thing?

450
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:04,300
Like you, we here at the Channel 10
newsroom felt that big jolt this morning.

451
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,500
It was a powerful earthquake.

452
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:09,900
We're having trouble
contacting emergency officials...

453
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:12,700
Put your seat belt on, honey. Remember?

454
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:20,600
That's OK, baby. There you go.

455
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,300
I wanna go home.

456
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:28,300
We're going to
the safest room in town, I promise.

457
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,200
- Operations.
- Yes, this is Roark.

458
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,200
- Got Roark, line one.
