00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:47,400
The rest of you guys, along this bus.

710
00:50:47,600 --> 00:50:48,900
Come here.

711
00:50:49,100 --> 00:50:51,000
All right, on the countdown, aim low.

712
00:50:51,100 --> 00:50:53,400
Three, two, one, fire.

713
00:50:58,400 --> 00:51:01,800
All right, we know that stuff is lava.
What do I do next?

714
00:51:02,100 --> 00:51:06,000
You have to evacuate the West Side. This'll
burn through the city till it hits the ocean.

715
00:51:06,300 --> 00:51:10,100
- It has a million people.
- There'll be a million dead or homeless.

716
00:51:10,300 --> 00:51:14,700
This is going to destroy
everything it touches.

717
00:51:20,100 --> 00:51:22,600
- He's still breathing. Can you grab this arm?
- Yeah.

718
00:51:22,700 --> 00:51:24,200
Grab him right there.

719
00:51:26,100 --> 00:51:27,400
Let's go, let's go!

720
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:28,700
Let's get this guy out.

721
00:51:28,900 --> 00:51:32,200
Are you realising what we're dealing with?
This is a volcano.

722
00:51:32,400 --> 00:51:35,800
- All we can do is get out of its way.
- Run for the hills and hide?

723
00:51:36,100 --> 00:51:37,500
- Right.
- I can't do that.

724
00:51:37,700 --> 00:51:38,600
Look out!

725
00:51:38,700 --> 00:51:39,500
Look out!

726
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:53,100
Stay with this guy. Stay with him.

727
00:51:53,300 --> 00:51:55,200
Hey, get that ladder over here now!

728
00:51:58,300 --> 00:51:59,300
Bring it down!

729
00:51:59,500 --> 00:52:02,300
- What're you gonna do?
- Get us outta here if I can.

730
00:52:02,500 --> 00:52:05,600
Hey, watch out for those flames!

731
00:52:05,700 --> 00:52:09,700
Get that ladder out of the fire!
The hose is gonna burn!

732
00:52:10,000 --> 00:52:13,600
- Clear!
- Ah!

733
00:52:13,900 --> 00:52:16,300
- Outta here. Move!
- We're not gonna do this.

734
00:52:16,400 --> 00:52:18,500
Pull him out!

735
00:52:18,700 --> 00:52:20,200
- Move!
- Oh, my God.

736
00:52:23,100 --> 00:52:24,600
- Oh, God. Oh, God.
- Hang on.

737
00:52:24,700 --> 00:52:27,900
- Push him in!
- I can't. The ladder's bust. Too much weight.

738
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:31,100
- I'm gonna have to swing 'em over.
- Move it!

739
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:36,400
- Couldn't he swing us the other way?
- I'll ask him when we get down.

740
00:52:36,800 --> 00:52:40,400
The hose is burning! The hose is on fire!

741
00:52:40,600 --> 00:52:42,600
- Argh!
- Shit!

742
00:52:42,700 --> 00:52:44,800
- Hold on!
- I'm holding on!

743
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:47,400
Faster. Move it. They're cookin' up there!

744
00:52:47,600 --> 00:52:50,100
My feet are burning! My feet are burning!

745
00:52:50,400 --> 00:52:53,400
Keep the guy still!
The ladder's gonna give!

746
00:52:53,600 --> 00:52:56,800
- My foot!
- Keep it still!

747
00:52:56,900 --> 00:53:00,700
- The ladder's going. We're losing it.
- Keep still! You're moving us!

748
00:53:02,100 --> 00:53:03,500
- Move it.
- Hang on!

749
00:53:03,700 --> 00:53:05,500
Stop kicking! Argh!

750
00:53:09,200 --> 00:53:11,000
Oh!

751
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:12,600
Oh, my God!

752
00:53:15,000 --> 00:53:18,900
This guy needs oxygen!
Get him over to Cedars right away.

753
00:53:19,100 --> 00:53:19,900
You all right?

754
00:53:21,700 --> 00:53:23,900
Oh... I'm sorry. Sorry.

755
00:53:24,100 --> 00:53:27,000
- Are you all right!?
- Yeah, I've never been better.

756
00:53:27,200 --> 00:53:29,200
So, what do we do now? Come on.

757
00:54:00,800 --> 00:54:02,600
That lava is coming from a vent.

758
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:06,800
Bad news is there could be other vents,
bigger ones, maybe ten times as big,

759
00:54:06,900 --> 00:54:10,000
which means we may not have seen
the main eruption yet.

760
00:54:10,300 --> 00:54:13,400
- You think that's gonna happen?
- I need specifics, a phone.

761
00:54:13,600 --> 00:54:15,600
- Your phone! Give me that.
- Hey! I need that back.

762
00:54:15,800 --> 00:54:19,700
- I'm on the air. I need that back.
- Stay where you are. Stay where you are!

763
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:23,200
- Hey, lava's moving round the bus!
- Give me that phone.

764
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:26,400
- Hey, that's property of KNX.
- Not any more, pal.

765
00:54:27,600 --> 00:54:31,100
All right, Emmit,
get me 200 K-rails to build a corridor.

766
00:54:31,300 --> 00:54:34,100
- What are K-rails?
- They're concrete freeway dividers.

767
00:54:34,300 --> 00:54:36,000
You planning on channelling this?

768
00:54:36,200 --> 00:54:38,300
- I'm on the telephone, all right.
- Sorry.

769
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:41,300
Mike, I'll call Public Works.
They could have some.

770
00:54:41,500 --> 00:54:44,300
- Roark?
- Yeah, and any private contractor we have...

771
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:45,200
Roark!

772
00:54:51,100 --> 00:54:52,200
Hell!

773
00:54:53,200 --> 00:54:57,200
And call Gator. Cedars is gonna be swamped.
I want him over there.

774
00:54:57,500 --> 00:54:59,100
You don't want him with you?

775
00:54:59,300 --> 00:55:01,500
No, Kelly is on her way to Cedars now.

776
00:55:01,700 --> 00:55:02,900
She got burnt, Emmit.

777
00:55:04,400 --> 00:55:05,400
Shit.

778
00:55:05,500 --> 00:55:08,400
She'll have a suite
by the time the sun comes up, all right?

779
00:55:08,700 --> 00:55:09,900
All right. Out. What?

780
00:55:09,900 --> 00:55:12,500
The bus is just deflecting this, OK?

781
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:17,800
It is coming back around. It's got in the store.
We are dealing with determined stuff here.

782
00:55:18,200 --> 00:55:21,200
All right,
we'll build berms until the K-rails get here.

783
00:55:21,400 --> 00:55:24,600
- With what?
- We'll dig up the streets, we'll improvise.

784
00:55:29,600 --> 00:55:35,400
Literally hundreds of firemen,
police, city workers have grabbed pickaxes

785
00:55:35,800 --> 00:55:39,200
to try to channel this down...

786
00:55:39,400 --> 00:55:43,400
..the ash and the smoke in the air right now.

787
00:55:43,700 --> 00:55:46,400
..to make a dentin this latest attack on LA.

788
00:55:46,600 --> 00:55:49,600
That wall has to be five or six metres tall.
Stay with it.

789
00:55:49,900 --> 00:55:54,200
It's hitting every street. We've got
structural fires and inhalation cases.

790
00:55:54,500 --> 00:55:56,400
- I can't keep it out without help.
- I'm working on it.

791
00:55:56,500 --> 00:56:01,700
Meantime, do all you can to keep it
on Wilshire. Use fire trucks, if you have to.

792
00:56:02,100 --> 00:56:06,000
My street's on fire.
You gotta get some trucks down there.

793
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:09,600
- What street?
- The one with smoke coming out. Stanley.

794
00:56:09,900 --> 00:56:13,000
- Once this is under control.
- There won't be houses left by then!

795
00:56:13,100 --> 00:56:15,500
Look, I'm sorry. We'll get to 'em when we can.

796
00:56:15,800 --> 00:56:19,300
Yo, I'm talking about people's houses.
You're up here saving museums.

797
00:56:19,600 --> 00:56:21,200
D'you wanna get this guy off me?

798
00:56:21,400 --> 00:56:24,400
- Oh, great. Mark Fuhrman.
- Let me see your hands.

799
00:56:24,600 --> 00:56:26,400
- You gotta be joking.
- Give me your hands!

800
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:29,600
Get your goddamn hands off me!

801
00:56:29,800 --> 00:56:31,100
Hey, what's going on?

802
00:56:31,300 --> 00:56:34,800
- He was harassing a firefighter.
- Bullshit. I was asking for help.

803
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:37,300
- This is stupid. Let him go.
- I'm taking him in.

804
00:56:37,500 --> 00:56:38,900
Aw, he's all yours.

805
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:41,900
- Shouldn't you be saving lives?
- Don't move!

806
00:56:42,100 --> 00:56:46,400
Watch that third rail.
I don't want anybody hitting that.

807
00:56:46,700 --> 00:56:49,700
Hey, watch for the rubble right there!
Watch for the rubble.

808
00:56:51,900 --> 00:56:53,800
Oh, Jesus.

809
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:57,000
- There she is.
- Looks like we got a hell of a fire, Stan.

810
00:56:57,100 --> 00:56:58,000
Yeah, we sure do.

811
00:56:58,200 --> 00:57:00,400
Right, let's go, let's go, double time!

812
00:57:00,500 --> 00:57:04,500
It can't be gas, they turned off
the whole quadrant. Gotta be electrical.

813
00:57:04,700 --> 00:57:09,100
Call LAFD! Tell them there's a fire
500 yards from MacArthur Park station!

814
00:57:09,400 --> 00:57:13,700
Get those first-aid kits
and those oxygen masks down here now!

815
00:57:14,000 --> 00:57:16,000
Here, give me that.

816
00:57:16,500 --> 00:57:18,600
Come on. Hit it.

817
00:57:20,300 --> 00:57:22,500
Come on, hit it!

818
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:28,400
Oh, my God.

819
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:33,600
Give me a push.

820
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:38,300
- Let's check these people out in here.
- Check 'em out.

821
00:57:38,600 --> 00:57:40,400
I got a pulse! Get the other one.

822
00:57:40,500 --> 00:57:43,700
How many we got?
Give me a count here! Give me a count!

823
00:57:44,000 --> 00:57:45,300
Some oxygen up here.

824
00:57:47,700 --> 00:57:49,200
Stan.

825
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:51,100
Just a second. Just a second.

826
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:52,000
Stan!

827
00:57:52,200 --> 00:57:55,400
Let's get everybody out on the station floor.

828
00:57:55,500 --> 00:57:57,500
What you got, Pete?

829
00:57:59,300 --> 00:58:01,000
What the hell is that?

830
00:58:08,300 --> 00:58:09,500
Get off the train...

831
00:58:09,600 --> 00:58:11,300
Get off the train! Get off the train!

832
00:58:11,500 --> 00:58:15,200
Every one of these bodies off the train now!
Fireman's carry, go, go!

833
00:58:15,400 --> 00:58:18,400
- We can't get 'em all.
- Anybody see the driver?

834
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:20,500
Give me your gloves.

835
00:58:20,700 --> 00:58:23,200
- What're you doing?
- I gotta find the driver.

836
00:58:23,400 --> 00:58:28,000
Every one of these people off the train now.
Come on, move it! Move it! Go! Go!

837
00:58:29,800 --> 00:58:31,300
Stan, get back here!

838
00:58:34,100 --> 00:58:39,200
We are in the parking lot at Cedars Sinai
and this is an incredible scene.

839
00:58:39,600 --> 00:58:42,200
These people are staying in the parking lot

840
00:58:42,300 --> 00:58:46,000
because the emergencyroom
is filled to capacity.

841
00:58:46,100 --> 00:58:49,100
The injuredjustkeep coming here
one afteranother.

842
00:58:49,500 --> 00:58:55,800
This, to me, seems more like a MASH unit
than a majormetropolitan hospital...

843
00:58:56,100 --> 00:58:57,900
Yeah?

844
00:58:58,100 --> 00:59:00,100
- Gator, you got my girl?
- Right here.

845
00:59:00,300 --> 00:59:03,600
- Doc says she's gonna be fine.
- Nearly done.

846
00:59:03,900 --> 00:59:06,300
All right, let me talk to her.

847
00:59:12,100 --> 00:59:15,900
Man's got a direct line to the governor,
but he's calling you.

848
00:59:16,200 --> 00:59:20,800
- I'm fine, Daddy. Honestly,... I'm OK.
- This is gonna sting.

849
00:59:21,100 --> 00:59:22,500
OK?

850
00:59:24,000 --> 00:59:26,700
- I love you, baby.
- Then stop sending us bodies.

851
00:59:26,900 --> 00:59:30,100
- We have gota full house overhere.
- I don't have any choice.

852
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:35,500
Cedars Sinai is the only emergency room
that's still safe and north of the flow.

853
00:59:35,800 --> 00:59:39,200
We got earthquake victims,
burns, smoke inhalations.

854
00:59:39,400 --> 00:59:41,800
They're doing triage on the sidewalk.

855
00:59:41,900 --> 00:59:46,100
Put the post-ops in the mall.
Beverly Center's gotta have its own power.

856
00:59:46,400 --> 00:59:47,900
- The mall, huh?
- Yeah.

857
00:59:48,100 --> 00:59:49,400
Anything good at the cineplex?

858
00:59:51,100 --> 00:59:53,100
Have the cops close the streets for you.

859
00:59:58,000 --> 01:00:00,000
Oh, goddammit.

860
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:03,100
Jesus H Christ.

861
01:00:04,700 --> 01:00:07,400
- See that? The flow's gonna turn.
- Yeah, I saw it.

862
01:00:07,500 --> 01:00:11,200
- What's south of here, Lieutenant?
- Convalescent homes, hospitals.

863
01:00:11,300 --> 01:00:15,500
I'll tell you. A big gas station,
a million houses and everyone I know.

864
01:00:15,700 --> 01:00:18,200
Get back in there.
We need everybody we can get.

865
01:00:18,400 --> 01:00:19,200
Shit!

866
01:00:19,400 --> 01:00:22,500
Emmit, where are those K-rails?
I need 'em right now.

867
01:00:22,700 --> 01:00:26,700
Hey, what were you trying to do?
Take that guy downtown?

868
01:00:27,100 --> 01:00:30,500
- Better take the freeway. Wilshire looks bad.
- Hey, enough!

869
01:00:30,500 --> 01:00:32,800
Let's get these people on the cart.

870
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:36,000
Come on, Stan. Come on, Stan.
Where the hell are you?

871
01:01:12,900 --> 01:01:16,000
Holy Mary, mother of God, pray for us sinners
now and at the hour of our death.

872
01:01:16,200 --> 01:01:18,700
Hail Mary, full of grace, the Lord is with thee.

873
01:01:21,000 --> 01:01:25,100
Holy Mary, mother of God, pray for us sinners
now and at the hour of our death.

874
01:01:25,400 --> 01:01:29,000
Hail Mary, full of grace, the Lord is with thee.
Blessed art thou amongst women,

875
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:33,000
and blessed is the fruit of thy womb.
Holy Mary, mother of God...

876
01:01:33,100 --> 01:01:36,700
- Get on the walkie...
- Hey, it's Stan!

877
01:01:40,800 --> 01:01:43,700
Jump, Stan! Come on, Stan! Go!

878
01:01:44,900 --> 01:01:46,700
Stan, get outta there!

879
01:01:46,900 --> 01:01:48,200
Jump!

880
01:01:48,300 --> 01:01:52,600
- Get outta here!
- No, Stan! You can't save him!

881
01:01:52,900 --> 01:01:54,300
Come on, jump!

882
01:01:57,100 --> 01:01:59,900
- Come on!
- Come on! Save yourself!

883
01:02:02,000 --> 01:02:03,400
No!

884
01:02:10,600 --> 01:02:12,200
Aaahhhhhhh!

885
01:02:14,800 --> 01:02:17,800
Aaahhh!

886
01:02:18,100 --> 01:02:18,900
Ah!

887
01:02:28,200 --> 01:02:31,600
- Emmit, FAA want an update.
- Where are we with the airports?

888
01:02:31,800 --> 01:02:35,100
No more outgoing.
Incoming is being re-routed to Ontario.

889
01:02:35,300 --> 01:02:37,100
No, no, no, no. Marty, no.

890
01:02:37,300 --> 01:02:42,200
Look at the screen. That cloud is blowing due
east. We gotta send everything to San Diego.

891
01:02:42,400 --> 01:02:47,800
Emmit, they got two gas lines burning on
Fairfax. They can't get any hydrant pressure.

892
01:02:48,000 --> 01:02:49,600
- Swimming pools.
- What about them?

893
01:02:49,800 --> 01:02:53,800
Pump out all the swimming pools.
That's all the water we need.

894
01:02:54,000 --> 01:02:58,000
Emmit, just got a call from La Brea.
Total gridlock from Pico to Sunset.

895
01:02:58,200 --> 01:03:01,700
- Didn't we send over those traffic cops?
- That's who's calling.

896
01:03:02,000 --> 01:03:04,200
Cars keep stalling out because of the ash.

897
01:03:04,300 --> 01:03:07,100
- It's clogging up the air filters.
- Chevettes, right?

898
01:03:09,700 --> 01:03:13,000
OK, nowyou can see it coming rightat us.

899
01:03:13,200 --> 01:03:19,400
Just a relentless tide oflava melting the street
itself. Itincinerates everything it touches.

900
01:03:19,700 --> 01:03:23,600
They're using concrete, they're using cars,...

901
01:03:23,900 --> 01:03:28,200
- You gotta get me some water pressure!
- I can't. The city's out.

902
01:03:28,500 --> 01:03:30,700
- Hydrants are dry!
- Lights are out in San Francisco.

903
01:03:30,900 --> 01:03:33,900
- We gotta get these guys some help.
- Yeah, I can see that.

904
01:03:35,400 --> 01:03:39,400
Don't you hear me?
I said the lights are out in San Francisco.

905
01:03:39,600 --> 01:03:43,500
But this street's on fire.
Nobody gives a shit about San Francisco!

906
01:04:05,600 --> 01:04:08,100
All right, good to see you.

907
01:04:08,300 --> 01:04:13,300
We want a corridor outta these K-rails. Keep it
flowing down Wilshire and headed west, OK?

908
01:04:13,600 --> 01:04:15,800
- Where are the rest of them?
- This is it.

909
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:20,000
- There's only about 80 here.
- 82. Everything else is stuck on the 5 or 10.

910
01:04:20,300 --> 01:04:23,700
We're trying to keep the city in one piece.
80 rails won't do it!

911
01:04:23,700 --> 01:04:25,800
- What you blaming me for?
- Convenience!

912
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:29,200
- Maybe we can chopper more in?
- One at at time, forget it!

913
01:04:29,500 --> 01:04:33,600
Why not knock down a couple of buildings
and block this son of a bitch?

914
01:04:33,900 --> 01:04:35,800
All right, come with me.

915
01:04:35,800 --> 01:04:37,600
You guys, come with me.

916
01:04:39,200 --> 01:04:41,600
- Open a reservoir!
- And the city drinks what?!

917
01:04:41,800 --> 01:04:44,300
- There won't be a city, ifyou don't move.
- I'm doing my best!

918
01:04:44,400 --> 01:04:47,100
Knock this shit off! What is with you people?

919
01:04:47,300 --> 01:04:50,000
Chief, how long will it take this stuff
to get to Fairfax?

920
01:04:50,200 --> 01:04:54,900
- About ten minutes, give or take.
- Enough time to build a barricade?

921
01:04:58,100 --> 01:05:03,000
All right, look.
Wilshire Boulevard, Fairfax.

922
01:05:03,300 --> 01:05:05,600
80 K-rails, double stacked in a horseshoe.

923
01:05:05,700 --> 01:05:06,600
OK?

924
01:05:07,900 --> 01:05:09,000
A cul-de-sac.

925
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:12,500
That's gotta be a wall at least 6ft high.

926
01:05:12,700 --> 01:05:16,600
- D'you have any helicopters, water tankers?
- Not yet, but they're on the way.

927
01:05:16,700 --> 01:05:22,100
Once you get this lava to pool, dump
everything on it, all at once, to form a crust.

928
01:05:22,500 --> 01:05:24,600
Maybe it'll dam itself like one did in lceland.

929
01:05:25,700 --> 01:05:27,900
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

930
01:05:28,000 --> 01:05:30,200
This is putting a Band-Aid on a broken leg.

931
01:05:30,300 --> 01:05:33,400
I don't know how many men
to keep putting in front of this thing.

932
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:35,100
As many people as it takes.

933
01:05:35,300 --> 01:05:37,800
Listen up, let me tell you what's south of us.

934
01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:42,500
No more museums or department stores,
just homes, people.

935
01:05:42,800 --> 01:05:44,800
If we run now, they're defenceless.

936
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:48,700
You don't like my plan, give me another one,
